File: The number of confirmed coronavirus cases has risen to 12,047. JOHANNESBURG - The COVID-19 death toll has risen to 219. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the announcement during an address to the nation on Wednesday night. Ramaphosa said the virus has taken a toll on South Africans. LIVESTREAM: President Ramaphosa addresses the nation "This virus is taking a heavy toll not only on our people's health, but their ability to earn a living, learn, develop and enjoy basic freedoms we take for granted," he said. The number of confirmed coronavirus cases has risen to 12,047. Of those, 4,745 patients have recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.